	<div class="excerpt">
		<p>For Session 4 of TED2024, illuminators from diverse disciplines explored the bright future of their fields. From AI as a digital species to explosive art that climbs into the sky, speakers looked at how light (literally and figuratively) can shape our climate, social interactions, scientific discoveries and more. The event: Talks from Session 4 of <a class="read-more" title="Read more" href="https://blog.ted.com/illuminators-notes-on-session-4-of-ted2024/">[<span>&hellip;</span>]</a></p>
	</div>

</article>			
<article id="post-116872" class="post-116872 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-live-from-ted2024 category-news-2 category-ted2024 tag-daniela-rus tag-hiroki-koga tag-karthik-muralidharan tag-pete-stavros tag-rumman-chowdhury tag-ted tag-ted-conferences tag-ted-talks tag-ted2024 tag-zeynep-ton has-thumbnail not-featured even i-10 clearfix" role="article">

